{"lemma": "حَيْثُ", "slug": "حَيْثُ", "root": "ح.#.ث", "root_slug": "ح-_-ث", "root_link": "/words/roots/ح-_-ث", "pos": "CONJ", "pos_camel": "conj", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "حَيْثُ", "root": "حيث", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 31}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["conj"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 4}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n9698"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D8%AB%D9%8F"}}, "translations": {"en": "where", "fa": "جایی که", "ur": "جہاں", "tr": "nerede", "id": "di mana", "bn": "যেখানে", "es": "donde", "fr": "où", "de": "wo", "ru": "где", "zh": "哪里"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "conj", "gloss": "where (relative)"}, {"pos": "conj", "gloss": "wherever; at any place", "examples": [{"text": "وَإِذْ قُلْنَا ٱدْخُلُوا هَٰذِهِ ٱلْقَرْيَةَ فَكُلُوا مِنْهَا حَيْثُ شِئْتُمْ رَغَدًا وَٱدْخُلُوا ٱلْبَابَ سُجَّدًا وَقُولُوا حِطَّةٌ نَغْفِرْ لَكُمْ خَطَايَاكُمْ وَسَنَزِيدُ ٱلْمُحْسِنِينَ"}]}, {"pos": "conj", "gloss": "since, whereas, due to the fact that"}, {"pos": "conj", "gloss": "because"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/ħaj.θu/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n9698", "headword_ar": "حَيْثُ", "root": "Hyv", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb, Mughnee, K,) indecl., (S, Msb,) with damm for its termination, (S, Msb, Mughnee,) as being likened to final words [such as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qabolu", "text_ar": "قَبْلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "baEodu", "text_ar": "بَعْدُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "ending a proposition], (S, Mughnee,) because it does not [regularly] occur otherwise than prefixed to a proposition, (S,) for the being prefixed to a proposition is like the not being prefixed to anything, as the consequence of being prefixed, which is the sign of the gen. case, is not apparent: (Mughnee:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayova", "text_ar": "حَيْثَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Mughnee, K,) also indecl., (S,) with fet-h, (S, Mughnee,) to render the pronunciation more easy, (Mughnee,) because damm with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Y", "text_ar": "ى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is deemed difficult to pronounce: (S:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayovi", "text_ar": "حَيْثِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Mughnee, K,) with kesr, accord. to the general rule observed to prevent the concurrence of two quiescent letters: (Mughnee:) and in like manner,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hawovu", "text_ar": "حَوْثُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hawova", "text_ar": "حَوْثَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hawovi", "text_ar": "حَوْثِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Mughnee, TA:) of which forms,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hwv", "text_ar": "حوث"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is asserted to be the original; (L;) though"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayovu", "text_ar": "حَيْثُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is more chaste than"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hawovu", "text_ar": "حَوْثُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and is the form used in the Kur-án: (Az and TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hwv", "text_ar": "حوث"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ":) but some of the Arabs make"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hyv", "text_ar": "حيث"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "decl.: (Mughnee:) it is an adverbial noun of place, (S, Msb,) a vague adverbial noun of place, (L,) [signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Where,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hiyna", "text_ar": "حِينَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "with respect to time: (S, K:) or it is a denotative of place, by general consent: but accord. to Akh it sometimes occurs as denoting time, [signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "when,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] as in the following verse, (Mughnee, TA,) which is the strongest evidence of its use in this sense: (TA:)"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "HayovamaA tasotaqimo yuqad~iro laka A@ll~`\n                      \n                     \n                        hu najaAHFA fiY gaAbiri AlA^azomaAni"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Whenever thou shalt pursue a right course, God will decree thee success in the time to come"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (Mughnee, TA:) but in most instances it occupies the place of an accus., as an adverbial noun of place; or of a gen., governed by"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino", "text_ar": "مِنْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and sometimes by another prep., as in the saying (of Zuheyr, TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "q$Em", "text_ar": "قشعم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "),"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "ladaY Hayovu A^aloqato raHolahaAA^um~u qa$oEami"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "At the place where Calamity,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Fate, has put down her saddle,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "made her abode"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: and sometimes it occurs as an objective complement, as it is said to do in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aall~`hu A^aEolamu Hayovu yajoEalu risaAlaAtihi", "text_ar": "اَللّٰهُ اَعْلَمُ حَيْثُ يَجْعَلُ رِسَالَاتِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[in the Kur vi. 124], i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "God is knowing:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "He knows"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "where to bestow his apostolic commissions;"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaEolamu", "text_ar": "يَعْلَمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being suppressed, as implied by"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEolamu", "text_ar": "اَعْلَمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aEolamu", "text_ar": "اَعْلَمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "may be rendered by"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaAlimN", "text_ar": "عَالِمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and so may govern the accus. case. (Mughnee.) Accord. to rule, (Mughnee,) in every instance, (S, Mughnee,) it is prefixed to a proposition, (S, Msb, Mughnee,) nominal, or verbal, but in most cases the latter; (Mughnee;) as in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aquwmu Hayovu yaquwmu zayodN", "text_ar": "اَقُومُ حَيْثُ يَقُومُ زَيْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I will stand where Zeyd shall stand"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayovu takuwnu", "text_ar": "حَيْثُ تَكُونُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^akuwnu", "text_ar": "اَكُونُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Where thou shalt be, I will be"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (S;) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "jalasotu Hayovu zayodFA A^araAhu", "text_ar": "جَلَسْتُ حَيْثُ زَيْدًا اَرَاهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I sat where I saw Zeyd"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], the accus. case being preferred in an instance like this; (Mughnee;) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A*ohabo Hayovu $y^ota", "text_ar": "اذْهَبْ حَيْثُ شيْتَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Go thou whither thou wilt."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (Msb in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayn", "text_ar": "حَين"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) You should not say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayovu zayodN", "text_ar": "حَيْثُ زَيْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[alone]: (S:) or it occurs prefixed to a single word in poetry; (Msb, Mughnee;) as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "wanaToEunuhumo taHota AlkulaY baEoda Darobihimo\n                      \n                     \n                        bibiyDi AlmawaADiY Hayovu laY~i AlEamaAy^imi"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And we pierce them beneath the kidneys, after smiting them, with the sharp swords, where the turbans are wound"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (Mughnee;) but this is irregular; (Msb, Mughnee;) though Ks holds it to be regular. (Mughnee.) Lh relates, on the authority of Ks, that some make"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hyv", "text_ar": "حيث"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to govern a noun in the gen. case, as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "A^amaA taraY Hayovu suhayolK TaAliEaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Seest thou not where Canopus is, rising?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: but he says that this is not of respectable authority: (L:) some write"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayova suhayolK", "text_ar": "حَيْثَ سُهَيْلٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and some,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayovu", "text_ar": "حَيْثُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "suhayolN", "text_ar": "سُهَيْلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [which is the common reading,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "shyl", "text_ar": "سهيل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being an inchoative, and] the enunciative,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mawojuwdN", "text_ar": "مَوْجُودٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", being suppressed. (Mughnee.) Abu-l-Fet-h says that he who prefixes"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hyv", "text_ar": "حيث"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to a single word makes it declinable. (Mughnee.) [Accord. to Fei,] BenooTemeem say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayova", "text_ar": "حَيْثَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "when it occupies the place of an accus., as in the phrase,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qumo Hayova yaquwmu zayodN", "text_ar": "قُمْ حَيْثَ يَقُومُ زَيْدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Stand thou where Zeyd shall stand"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Msb.) Ks says, I have heard among Benoo-Temeem, of Benoo-Yarbooa and Tuheiyeh, those who say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayova", "text_ar": "حَيْثَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in every case, when it occupies the place of a gen., and that of an accus., and that of a nom.; saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino Hayova laAyaEolamuwna", "text_ar": "مِنْ حَيْثَ لَايَعْلَمُونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Whence they know not"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayova A@lotaqayonaA", "text_ar": "حَيْثَ ا@لْتَقَيْنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Where we met"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: and he says also, I have heard some of Benu-l-HárithIbn-Asad-Ibn-El-Hárith-Ibn-Thaalabeh, and all Benoo-Fak'as, say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayovi", "text_ar": "حَيْثِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "when it occupies the place of a gen., and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayova", "text_ar": "حَيْثَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "when it occupies the place of an accus.; saying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino Hayovi laA yaEolamuwna", "text_ar": "مِنْ حَيْثِ لَا يَعْلَمُونَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayova A@lotaqayonaA", "text_ar": "حَيْثَ ا@لْتَقَيْنَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (L.) Sometimes the proposition after"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hyv", "text_ar": "حيث"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "commences with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~a", "text_ar": "اـِنَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as in"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aijoliso Hayovu", "text_ar": "اِجْلِسْ حَيْثُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~a zayodFA jaAlisN", "text_ar": "اـِنَّ زَيْدًا جَالِسٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Sit thou where Zeyd is sitting"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (K in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^n", "text_ar": "ان"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and IAk p. 92.) ―         -b2-  It sometimes comprises the meanings of two adverbial nouns of place, as when you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayovu Eabodu A@ll~`hi qaAEidN zayodN qaAy^imN", "text_ar": "حَيْثُ عَبْدُ ا@للّٰهِ قَاعِدٌ زَيْدٌ قَايِمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Where' Abd-Allah is sitting, there Zeyd is standing"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (AHeyth, L.) ―         -b3-  The restrictive"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA", "text_ar": "مَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA", "text_ar": "مَا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kaAf~apN", "text_ar": "كَافَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") is sometimes affixed to it, and in this case it implies a conditional meaning, [signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Wherever,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "wheresoever,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and, accord. to Akh,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whenever,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "whensoever,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (Mughnee, TA,) and renders two verbs mejzoom, (Mughnee,) as in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HayovumaA tajoliso A^ajoliso", "text_ar": "حَيْثُمَا تَجْلِسْ اَجْلِسْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Wherever thou shalt"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 684}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sit, I will sit"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (S,) and in the first of the verses cited above: (Mughnee, TA:) it is not [properly, though it is sometimes improperly,] used as a conditional without"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mA", "text_ar": "ما"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S.) ―         -b4-  [It is also used, in scientific and other post-classical works, in senses different from those explained above. Thus,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino Hayovu", "text_ar": "مِنْ حَيْثُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is used to signify"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "As to,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in respect of:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino Hayovu All~afoZi waAlmaEonaY", "text_ar": "مِنْ حَيْثُ اللَّفْظِ وَالمَعْنَى"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "As to,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in respect of, the word and the meaning."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "As,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "considered as, absolutely,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "abstractedly:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino Hayovu huwa", "text_ar": "مِنْ حَيْثُ هُوَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino", "text_ar": "مِنْ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hayovu huwa huwa", "text_ar": "حَيْثُ هُوَ هُوَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "As,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "considered as, such, absolutely,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "abstractedly;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA_inosaAnu mino Hayovu huwa", "text_ar": "الاـِنْسَانُ مِنْ حَيْثُ هُوَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_inosaAnN", "text_ar": "اـِنْسَانٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Man, as,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "considered as, man, absolutely,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "abstractedly."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "As,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "considered merely"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "only"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "simply as:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA_inosaAnu mino Hayovu A_in~ahu yaSiH~u watazuwlu Eanohu Als~iH~apu", "text_ar": "الاـِنْسَانُ مِنْ حَيْثُ اـِنَّهُ يَصِحُّ وَتَزُولُ عَنْهُ السِّحَّةُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mawoDuwEu AlT~ib~i", "text_ar": "مَوْضُوعُ الطِّبِّ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Man, as,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "considered merely"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "only"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "simply as, being healthy and ceasing to be healthy, is the object of therapeutics."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "As,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "since,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "because:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so in the saying,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aln~aAru mino Hayovu A_in~ahaA HaAr~apN tusax~inu AlmaA='a", "text_ar": "النَّارُ مِنْ حَيْثُ اـِنَّهَا حَارَّةٌ تُسَخِّنُ المَا=ءَ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Fire, as,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "since,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "because, it is hot, heats water."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biHayovu", "text_ar": "بِحَيْثُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is also vulgarly used in this sense. And correctly as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "So that; so as that; in such a state,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "condition, that:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "often"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "syn. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hat~aY", "text_ar": "حَتَّى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".]"}], "source_refs": ["S", "Msb", "L", "K", "TA"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}